inlineContent.text: Use the WebKit framework to integrate richly styled web content into your app’s native content. WebKit offers a full browsing experience for your content, offering a platform-native view and supporting classes to:
Display rich web content using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript
Handle the incremental loading of page content
Display multiple MIME types and compound frame elements
Manage a forward-back list of recently visited pages

object from your custom view hierarchies and load the content you want to display. Use supporting objects to manage cookies, evaluate scripts, control navigation, generate snapshots, and perform text-based searches.
Always call WebKit functions and methods from your app’s main thread or main dispatch queue.
